    <title>Client Libraries and Tools</title>
  <info>
    <raxm:metadata xmlns:raxm="http://docs.rackspace.com/api/metadata">      
      <raxm:type>concept</raxm:type>
      <raxm:product version="v1.0">cm</raxm:product>
      <raxm:priority>50</raxm:priority>
    </raxm:metadata> 
  </info>
  <?dbhtml stop-chunking?>
  <para>This section describes client libraries and tools that you can use to interact with the API. </para>

  <section xml:id="client-libraries">
    <title>Client Libraries</title>
    <section xml:id="client-libraries-rackspace-monitoring">
      <title>Python - <emphasis>"rackspace-monitoring"</emphasis> Library</title>
      <para>The official client library for interacting with the API is written in Python and based on
        the open-source <link xlink:href="http://libcloud.apache.org"
          >http://libcloud.apache.org</link> Apache Libcloud framework.</para>
      <para>Access the library from the following website:</para>
      <para><link xlink:href="https://github.com/racker/rackspace-monitoring"
          >https://github.com/racker/rackspace-monitoring</link></para>
      <para>Use the following command to install the library:</para>
      <programlisting>$ pip install rackspace-monitoring</programlisting>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="client-libraries-rackspace-monitoring-rb">
      <title>Ruby - <emphasis>"rackspace-monitoring"</emphasis> Library</title>
      <para>The official client library for interacting with the API is written in Ruby and based on
        the open-source <link xlink:href="http://fog.io/"
          >http://fog.io/</link> Fog library.</para>
      <para>Access the library from the following website:</para>
      <para><link xlink:href="https://github.com/racker/rackspace-monitoring-rb"
        >https://github.com/racker/rackspace-monitoring-rb</link></para>
      <para>Use the following command to install the library:</para>
      <programlisting>$ gem install rackspace-monitoring</programlisting>
    </section>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="client-tools">
    <title>Tools (CLI, etc...)</title>
    <section xml:id="client-tools-rackspace-monitoring-cli">
     <title>Command Line Interface - <emphasis>"Raxmon"</emphasis> Tool</title>
     <para>&MAAS; provides a command line utility for performing API actions.</para>
     <para>Access the library from the following website:</para>
     <para><link xlink:href="https://github.com/racker/rackspace-monitoring-cli"
         >https://github.com/racker/rackspace-monitoring-cli</link></para>
     <para>Use the following command to install the command line utility:</para>
     <programlisting>$ pip install --upgrade rackspace-monitoring-cli</programlisting>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="client-tools-rackspace-monitoring-chef">
      <title>Integration - <emphasis>"Cloud Monitoring Cookbook"</emphasis></title>
      <para>&MAAS; provides a cookbook for integrating with
        <link xlink:href="http://www.opscode.com/chef/">Opscode Chef</link>.</para>
      <para>Access the code and read some of the ways to use the
        integration here:</para>
      <para><link xlink:href="https://github.com/racker/cookbook-cloudmonitoring"
        >https://github.com/racker/cookbook-cloudmonitoring</link></para>
      <para>And here:</para>
      <para><link
          xlink:href="http://www.rackspace.com/knowledge_center/article/cloud-monitoring-automation-integrate-monitoring-with-chef"
          >http://www.rackspace.com/knowledge_center/article/cloud-monitoring-automation-integrate-monitoring-with-chef</link>
      </para>
      <para>Follow the instructions to install the Chef integration.</para>
    </section>
  </section>
